{
  "text": "[1998] may eventually be useful for calculating propagation delays since the study of solar wind phase front propagation is analogous in many ways to the study of magnetopause orientation and motion. In addition, [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] present state of the art techniques for studying magnetopause orientation based on single spacecraft boundary crossings just as one often has just a single monitor to sense interplanetary conditions and the same observations are those that would be used to estimate and correct for propagation delays. [CITATION_3] and [CITATION_4] also demonstrate how plasma density and flow data can be used to further constrain the determination of normals to discontinuities.",
